Sessions.Name: That's Not Us (Opening Night)
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Celebrate the opening of the 26th MQFF with our Opening Night Film That's Not Us and a party with DJ YO! MAFIA after the film.

Sessions.Name: Back On Board: Greg Louganis
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Louganis - the greatest diver ever - fights for financial security and to re-enter the sport that shunned him as gay and HIV-positive.

Sessions.Name: Portrait of a Serial Monogamist
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Elsie breaks up with her long-term girlfriend to pursue a crush, igniting the disapproval of her friends. This authentic Canadian comedy is set to be a festival favourite.

Sessions.Name: Addicted to Fresno
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Jamie Babbit's hilarious black comedy features Natasha Lyonne, Judy Greer, Fred Armisen, Aubrey Plaza & Molly Shannon.

Sessions.Name: Departure
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: A vacation in France becomes complicated for young Elliot and his mother (Juliet Stevenson) when a handsome local arrives.

Sessions.Name: Beautiful Something
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: In one euphoric, sensual night, three generations of men explore the interconnections between love and art.

Sessions.Name: Chemsex
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: An eye-opening, unflinching documentary exploring amphetamine use and increased HIV infections amongst this emerging gay subculture.

Sessions.Name: Queer Filmmaking Workshop
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: This workshop will provide the opportunity to learn fundamental filmmaking techniques in addition to discussing what it means to be a queer filmmaker.

Sessions.Name: Liz in September
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Womaniser Liz (Patricia Velasquez from The L Word), is instantly smitten when she meets a young and seemingly straight outsider.

Sessions.Name: Documentary Shorts
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: These remarkable true stories include parents raising a trans child, a church preaching marriage equality and a disabled man's search for love. Screens with Bedding Andrew, Elder, Elise, Queer Habits, Raising Ryland, The Bower Effect, The Typist

Sessions.Name: Girl-on-Girl Shorts
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: A connection at a house party, an awkward threesome or a relationship on the rocks, these shorts will enlighten, surprise and amuse. Screens with 09:55 - 11:05, INGRID EKMAN, BERGSGATAN 4B, Betty, No Matter Who, One Last Night, Step, The Escape Hatch

Sessions.Name: Deep Run
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Cole is a young trans man living in religious, rural North Carolina. Executive produced by Susan Sarandon, Deep Run is a powerful watch. Screens with Alexa To Exa

Sessions.Name: What is the future of Queer Film?
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: This free panel asks what it means to be a queer filmmaker, and what is queer filmmaking today and going forward.

Sessions.Name: Desert Migration
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Palm Springs is an oasis for HIV-positive older men escaping death, loss and the expense of living with long-term HIV.

Sessions.Name: Naz & Maalik
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Muslim teen, Naz is caught in a lie when he tries to hide the true nature of his relationship with best friend Maalik in this fresh New York-set film.

Sessions.Name: Grandma
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Lily Tomlin stars as a tough talking lesbian who hits the road with her troubled granddaughter who needs to get an abortion.

Sessions.Name: Hooking Up Shorts
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: The laws of desire are uncovered in this collection of short films that examine the various ways we connect, get it on and get off. Screens with Criticism, Glory Hole, No Strings, The Tricks List, Want It

Sessions.Name: Tab Hunter Confidential
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: In 1950s Hollywood, Tab Hunter was a studio-constructed, all-American heart throb and intensely private about his sexuality.

Sessions.Name: Lonely Stars
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Put-upon friends Joana and Valentina dream of fame and fortune but the path to success is littered with dead divas, fierce rivals, lesbian wrestlers and amorous crime bosses.

Sessions.Name: Closet Monster
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Traumatised by witnessing a gay bashing as a child, Oscar has ambivalent feelings towards his sexuality. He is thrown into disarray when he meets a charismatic co-worker.

Sessions.Name: Summer
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Anna falls for outsider Lena and must deal with small minded locals and family pressure in this authentic coming-of-age drama.

Sessions.Name: International Shorts
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: A diverse selection of award winning shorts with stories of infidelity, trans experiences, a trek through the desert and a homophobic soccer coach. Screens with Actresses, Laundry Mood, Pepper, The Forgiven, Thirst, Vessels

Sessions.Name: When My Sorrow Died - The Legend of Armen Ra & The Theremin
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Former drag queen, NY club kid and a consummate storyteller, the glamorously eccentric Armen Ra is a master of the theremin.

Sessions.Name: Scrum
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Muddy, sweaty and visually arresting, this intimate documentary follows the Sydney team to the international gay rugby union tournament. Screens with short film Boxeadora

Sessions.Name: La Belle Saison
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: This passionate love story traces the sexual and political awakening of a naive farmgirl who moves to Paris and falls in love with the beautiful radical feminist Carole.

Sessions.Name: Henry Gamble's Birthday Party
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Henry may be in lust with his best friend, and the cute drama geek may be in love with Henry in this drama about Christian middle-class America.

Sessions.Name: Boulevard
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Robin Williams stars as a closeted married man who develops feelings for a young rent boy in one of his last performances.

Sessions.Name: Ecco Homo
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Who is Peter 'Troy' Davies? Teenage prostitute, skinhead Sharpie, woman, post-punk figure, charming liar? Features friends Bono and Michael Hutchence.

Sessions.Name: Oriented
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: This compassionate portrait explores what it means to be Palestinian and gay and the politics of sexuality, pride and citizenship.

Sessions.Name: Girls Lost
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Three outcast teenage girls happen upon a mysterious plant that can change their gender overnight.

Sessions.Name: Movie Matchmaking
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Whether you're partnered, single or polyamorous, all film-loving queers and allies are welcome.

Sessions.Name: Hidden Away
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: A classic story of star-crossed lovers from different sides of the tracks; middle-class teen meets refugee facing deportation.

Sessions.Name: In the Grayscale
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Compared to Andrew Haigh's Weekend, this slow-burn Chilean drama has won acclaim for its naturalistic, sensual atmosphere.

Sessions.Name: Web Shorts
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Webseries episodes ranging from trans buddy comedies, lesbian rom-coms and the 'other' Kardashian. Find your next binge watch. Screens with Be Here Nowish, Brothers, Dyke Central, Kam Kardashian, Kelsey, McTucky Friend High, Pot Luck, Shakespeare Republic, Two JasperJohns, Wallflowers

Sessions.Name: The Summer of Sangaile
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Perfectly capturing the swoon of first love, this sensual teen romance of one fateful summer features an original soundtrack from FB Dunckel of Air.

Sessions.Name: Loev
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: A Wall Street dealmaker calls an old friend on his Mumbai business trip who drops everything - including his boyfriend - to join him.

Sessions.Name: Bare
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Dianna Agron (Glee) stars in this impressive debut feature with Paz de la Huerta. A gritty, sexy and sometimes psychedelic trip.

Sessions.Name: All Yours
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: A cam-boy gets a ticket to Belgium from a baker, and is expected to share his bed and work in the bakery. Flirtations with a female co-worker add strain to their home life.

Sessions.Name: The Glamour and the Squalor
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: One of the most important music icons you've never heard of, radio DJ Marco Collins broke 90's grunge bands like Nirvana & Pearl Jam.

Sessions.Name: Stuff
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: The marriage of a lesbian couple with children is on the rocks, and a friendship with a tattoo artist is becoming something more.

Sessions.Name: Mala Mala
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: An enlightening, award-winning documentary following trans-identifying subjects in Puerto Rico where macho Latino culture dominates.

Sessions.Name: Querelle (Melbourne Cinémathèque)
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Fassbinder's bold final film follows the murderous, criminal and sexual exploits of a young psychopathic sailor (Brad Davis).

Sessions.Name: Portrait of a Serial Monogamist
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Elsie breaks up with her long-term girlfriend to pursue a crush, igniting the disapproval of her friends. This authentic Canadian comedy is set to be a festival favourite.

Sessions.Name: The Bitter Tears of Petra Von Kant (Melbourne Cinémathèque)
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: This Fassbinder classic features an emotionally sadistic fashion designer and the women who visit her in her garish bedroom.

Sessions.Name: La Belle Saison
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: This passionate love story traces the sexual and political awakening of a naive farmgirl who moves to Paris and falls in love with the beautiful radical feminist Carole.

Sessions.Name: Eisenstein in Guanajuato
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: The ever surprising Peter Greenaway has created a kinetic biopic of Russia's greatest filmmaker, Sergio Eisenstein and his late sexual awakening in Mexico.

Sessions.Name: How to Win at Checkers (Every Time)
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Oat lives with his aunt and openly gay older brother who is the breadwinner with an upper-class boyfriend. As the Thai military draft draws nearer the tension escalates.

Sessions.Name: Henry Gamble's Birthday Party
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Henry may be in lust with his best friend, and the cute drama geek may be in love with Henry in this drama about Christian middle-class America.

Sessions.Name: Remembering the Man (Centrepiece)
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Remembering the Man is a moving documentary that chronicles the relationship between Conigrave and his long term partner John Caleo.

Sessions.Name: Like Cattle Towards Glow
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: 5 stories feature a motley crew of young men traversing dark, sexual desires. Wistful, depraved, hypnotic & challenging.

Sessions.Name: Front Cover

Sessions.Name: You're Killing Me
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: A YouTube comedian thinks his crush expressing murderous urges is funny - until his friends start disappearing.

Sessions.Name: Youth Shorts
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: This package features stories of what it means to be young and queer; an Indian girl contemplates her sexuality, a time-travelling closet and a trans teen finds his voice,  Screens with Big Time - My Doodled Diary, Charlotte, Closets, Noam, Swirl, Whittier Boulevard

Sessions.Name: Fassbinder - To Love Without Demands
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: A portrait of a furiously gifted artist grappling with his inner demons. Featuring interviews with collaborators, loved ones, and a candid Fassbinder.

Sessions.Name: Margarita, with a Straw
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Margarita, with a Straw is a rare exploration of sexuality and disability. A truly joyful film about loving yourself, and loving life.

Sessions.DescriptionBrief: MQFF 2016 Industry Day will explore key aspects of the filmmaking process, with a focus on financing and distribution.

Sessions.DescriptionBrief: This collection of international shorts features an array of men falling in love, embracing their dark side or just having a bit of fun. Screens with Amsterdam, I Really Like You, Like Hope, Nightstand, SAN CRISTÓBAL

Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Jo gives ghost tours in New Orleans. She starts having terrifying nightmares and a medium warns her about a vengeful spirit.

Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Essayist, novelist, filmmaker, activist, traveller, lover. Susan Sontag authored influential works. Followed by a panel discussion with Christos Tsiolkas.

Sessions.DescriptionBrief: A compilation of highlights from the various shorts packages throughout MQFF 2016; featuring a diverse range of genres, themes and voices. Screens with Bedding Andrew, Cake, Charlotte, Clown Service, Cruise Patrol, Thirst, Vessels

Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Retelling of Sweden's 16th century 'virgin queen' who brazenly flaunted her sexuality and fought for reform.

Sessions.Name: Dressed as a Girl
Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Enter the world of London's underground drag scene. Dressed as a Girl is a glorious mash of anarchy, art, sex, drugs and booze.

Sessions.DescriptionBrief: Adam enjoys hanging with his straight buddies, drinking beer and talking hockey. He also likes guys.
